      "text": "The architecture is super simple; Firehose is a fully serverless service from AWS that will soak in message and dump them to a destination of your choice when either the timeout is expired or the size limit is hit, whichever comes first. It's easy to setup and it's cheap. In this case I used the HTTP destination and configured it to push to New Relic's API; there's some docs available on AWS and New Relic's sites, I ended up following the one AWS [https://docs.aws.amazon.com/firehose/latest/dev/create-destination.html#create-destination-new-relic aws]"
